OL,6,FA neighbourhood in the seaside town of
OL,7,FRhyl has been named the most deprived
OL,8,Farea of Wales for the second time in
OL,9,Fsix years.
OL,11,FNew data released by the Welsh
OL,12,FGovernment shows that an area in Rhyl
OL,13,Ftown centre takes the unenviable top
OL,14,Fspot for the second time since 2019.
OL,16,FMeanwhile, Blaenau Gwent is the local
OL,17,Fauthority with the highest
OL,18,Fconcentration of the most deprived
OL,19,Fneighbourhoods in Wales (nine areas),
OL,20,Fwhile Monmouthshire was the only local
OL,21,Fauthority to have zero areas.
