OL,6,FMs Hutt added: "We are pleased the
OL,7,FChancellor has listened to our call in
OL,8,Frelation to welfare reform to scrap
OL,9,Fthe two-child limit, which will help
OL,10,Fto tackle the scourge of child
OL,11,Fpoverty. According to the UK
OL,12,FGovernment, the announcement will
OL,13,Fbring relief to 69,000 children in
OL,14,FWales who have previously been denied
OL,15,Ffinancial support from the UK benefits
OL,16,Fsystem. The publication of WIMD 2025
OL,17,Fwill ensure our efforts remain focused
OL,18,Fon where we can make the greatest
OL,19,Fdifference, helping to build a fairer
OL,20,Fand more equal Wales for all."
